
Event Listener to allow buttons to know when a user clicks

Inside index.js you want to add a function that does something when button gets clicked

> For example, adding the following would mean when you click the first button it will pop up with an alert

  document.querySelector("button").addEventListener("click", handleClick);

  function handleClick() {
      alert("I got clicked!");
  }

> OR for "anonymous function"

  document.querySelector("button").addEventListener("click", function () {
     alert("I got clicked!");
  });

> Code to then alert when clicking all buttons rather than just the first

Example A, cleanest version)
  document.querySelectorAll("button").forEach(function (button) {
    button.addEventListener("click", function () {
      alert("I got clicked!");
    });
  });

Example B)
  var buttons = document.querySelectorAll("button");

  for (var i = 0; i < buttons.length; i++) {
    buttons[i].addEventListener("click", function () {
      alert("I got clicked!");
    });
  }

Example C, coursework exact answer)
  var numberOfDrumButtons = document.querySelectorAll(".drum").length;
  
  for (var i = 0; i<numberOfDrumButtons; i++) {

    document.querySelectorAll(".drum") [i].addEventListener("click", function () {
        alert("I got clicked!");
    });

  }

